data.title: Canada Place
data.meta_description: Canada_Place - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Canada Place is a building in Vancouver, British Columbia that houses the Vancouver Convention Centre, Pan Pacific Vancouver Hotel, and serves as the main cruise ship terminal. It was built for Expo 86 and has a distinctive sail-like exterior. Canada Place also hosts community events and sounds horns daily at noon to play the first four notes of O Canada.
